TKT-Title: P2: Liquidfiles path exclusion in Defender ASR rule
TKT-Solution:
ASR rule “Block Office communication apps from creating child processes” was blocking the LiquidFiles agent. Added the path below to Intune Attack Surface Reduction Only Exclusions: C:\Program Files (x86)\LiquidFiles\LiquidFiles OutlookPlugin v3\LiquidFiles Windows Agent\LiquidFiles.Windows.AgentV3.exe

Policy pushed and confirmed applied. Agent now running normally.
Root cause: ASR policy block.
Status: Resolved.

TKT-Title: Failure Notification for Automate Patch Deployment task-Millennium - Auto Deployment Policy - Workstations
Request to Restart -Pop Up
TKT-Solution: Client reported restart reminder pop-ups reappearing every hour after patching. Verified Patch Manager Plus policy configuration. Behavior is expected and by design. Restart reminder is forced hourly until the device is rebooted to prevent patch backlog and ensure compliance. Some devices may not display the pop-up if no restart was required or they were already compliant. Explained this to client and confirmed the system is working as intended. Ticket resolved.

TKT-Title: Trojan Detected | PO-LT-JAMESH
TKT-Solution: The endpoint PO-LT-JAMESH was remediated following a Microsoft Defender alert for Trojan:JS/RedirOfbuse.ABAM!TB. Outlook was closed and the malicious OLK/attachment cache was cleared. Microsoft Defender was updated, and both a Quick Scan and a Full Scan were performed, confirming no active threats. Validation in PowerShell and Windows Security (Protection history) showed the Trojan was successfully remediated (ActionSuccess=True). A follow-up call with the user confirmed the system is clean and fully operational. The Ethernet adapter was re-enabled, and no further action is required.
